# --- GitHub Linguist language statistics ---
# This repository is a MyST/Markdown book, not a TeX or Python project.
# By default Linguist excludes Markdown (prose) from the language bar and then
# measures the few remaining support files, making the repo look like ~80%
# "TeX" (from refs.bib + custom.sty). Fix that:

# Count the Markdown prose so the bar reflects the actual book content.
*.md linguist-detectable

# Exclude build-support / data files that were skewing the stats.
shared/refs.bib   linguist-detectable=false
shared/custom.sty linguist-detectable=false

# --- Line-ending normalization ---
# Store text files with LF in the repo; check out native per platform.
# This makes behaviour explicit and stops the "LF will be replaced by CRLF"
# warnings on Windows.
* text=auto

# Binary assets: never normalize (prevents corruption and CRLF churn).
*.png   binary
*.pdf   binary
*.eps   binary
*.pstex binary
*.xlsx  binary
*.mw    binary
*.mws   binary
